entries.title: Inside Intel’s Delays in Delivering a Crucial New Microprocessor
entries.description: The company grappled with missteps for years while developing a microprocessor code-named Sapphire Rapids. It comes out on Tuesday.

entries.title: Coinbase Lays Off Another 20% of Employees
entries.description: The cuts at the cryptocurrency exchange come after nearly a fifth of employees were let go in June, as crypto markets teeter and tech companies rethink their growth plans.

entries.title: Three-Quarters of Teenagers Have Seen Online Pornography by Age 17
entries.description: Sexually explicit content has become so prevalent online that teenagers are deluged, according to a new report by a nonprofit child advocacy group.

entries.title: Brazil Riot and Jan. 6 Attack Followed a Similar Digital Playbook, Experts Say
entries.description: Researchers are studying how the internet was used to stoke anger and to organize far-right groups ahead of the Brazilian riots.
